window.bookSummaryJSON = "Award-winning author Rick Yancey has captivated young adult readers with his popular Alfred Kropp novels, the first of which was named a Best Book for Children by <i>Publishers Weekly</i> and was a finalist for the Carnegie Medal. Now Yancey begins a gripping new series with <i>The Monstrumologist</i>. <p>Dr. Warthrop is a scientist who tracks and studies real-life monsters. Assisted by his 12-year-old apprentice, Will Henry, Dr. Warthrop discovers a pod of Anthropophagi and launches a hunt to destroy the foul beasts.</p>"; 
